comment: Tucker (PHO) maintains legal guarding position and cleanly blocks Randolph's (MEM) driving layup attempt.
Leuer (PHO) sets the screen on Farmar (MEM) and gives him room to avoid the contact.
Tucker (PHO) and Stephenson (MEM) briefly engage and separate away from the ball.
Len (PHO) maintains legal guarding position as he defends Randolph's (MEM) drive and shot attempt.
Leuer (PHO) firms up as he sets the screen on Allen (MEM) and gives him room to avoid the contact.
Allen (PHO) cleanly knocks the ball away from Booker (PHO).
Farmar (MEM) maintains a legal guarding position as he defends Knight (PHO) on his drive.

Allen (MEM) makes incidental contact with Knight's (PHO) arm after he has released the shot and does not affect his follow-through. The players make leg contact that causes Knight to lose his balance.
Randolph (MEM) and Len (PHO) briefly engage and separate during rebounding.
Barnes (MEM) is in the paint without actively guarding an opponent for longer than three seconds.
Barnes (MEM) makes contact with Leuer's (PHO) arm that affects his driving shot attempt.
Booker (PHO) commits a take foul on Farmar (MEM).

Booker (PHO) commits a take foul on Allen (MEM). Even though the play originates in the back court, since Booker enters the front court before Allen, foul contact to the side of (or behind) is a common foul and not a clear path foul.
LHH shows that Barnes (MEM) cleanly blocks Leuer's (PHO) layup attempt.
